<h3 id=3D"GlobalGovernance|PD-GL-013ReleaseManagementProcess-MinimumRequire=
mentsforDeploymentsinProduction-Netsuite"><strong>Minimum Requirements for =
Deployments in Production - Netsuite</strong></h3>
<p>Regular Deployments in PD Environment (exception - Hotfixes* whose requi=
rements will be explained separately in this document) must be <strong>supp=
orted </strong>according to the following <strong>steps</strong>:</p>
<p></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Ticket in Jira to support the request</p></li>
<li>
<p>Functional Documentation <em>(system behavior</em>) and if applicable, T=
echnical Documentation also (System configuration, Script changes)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Test Matrix / Test Cases (referenced to Jira Ticket Number - It can be s=
upported in a separate document)</p></li>
<li>
<p>UAT: User Acceptance Test (this evidence must be supported by an e-mail =
or User=E2=80=99s OK as a comment in the ticket)</p></li>
</ol>
<p></p>
<h4 id=3D"GlobalGovernance|PD-GL-013ReleaseManagementProcess-ScriptsChanges=
">Scripts Changes</h4>
<p></p>
<p>If deployment involves a suitescript=E2=80=99s script whose impact is ch=
anging/adding/removing a functionality, the process that is described in th=
e link must be followed <a class=3D"external-link" data-card-appearance=3D"=
inline" href=3D"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1UAWR4pWvqBWwY5PFRwaDJp3=
9iE3oRflGkomlhnOs4KE/edit?usp=3Dsharing" rel=3D"nofollow">https://docs.goog=
le.com/document/d/1UAWR4pWvqBWwY5PFRwaDJp39iE3oRflGkomlhnOs4KE/edit?usp=3Ds=
haring</a> . Changes must NOT be executed through a script change in the fi=
le cabinet.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p></p>
<h3 id=3D"GlobalGovernance|PD-GL-013ReleaseManagementProcess-Approvers*"><s=
trong>Approvers*</strong></h3>
<p>Employees who are allowed to approve a Merge Request to Production.</p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Script</strong><br>
Octavio Manzano<br>
Rafael Natera</p>
<p>Ivan Macias<br>
Einis Rodriguez<br>
Omar Ortiz<br>
Wilmer Perez</p>
<p>Gonzalo Rodriguez</p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>*Note: Gitlab is adjusted to prevent that any user perform a sel=
f-approval. This must be restricted at a project level.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Configuration is setup in the following screen =E2=80=98Approval=
 Settings=E2=80=99.</strong></p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wra=
