<p></p>
<p><strong>New Fields requests, Custom Records, Forms,et</strong>c, that<em=
> do not require scripts </em>and given current limitations, manual bundlin=
g can=E2=80=99t be carried out (SDF or Bundle).</p>
<p></p>
<p>Employees that are allowed to approve MR: <br>
Employee that allowed to perform such manual editions</p>
<p>Frewuill Rodriguez</p>
<p>Aneriz Rodriguez<br></p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Hotfix</strong></p>
<p>*Ticket must be in place, but functional and technical documentation are=
 optional.&nbsp;</p>
<p></p>
<p>Employees that are allowed to approve MR:</p>
<p>Einis Rodriguez<br>
Uriel Ordo=C3=B1ez</p>
<p>Octavio Manzano</p>
<p><strong>Changes in Platform Configuration </strong>can only be executed =
by:<br>
Aneriz Rodriguez<br>
Frewuill Rodriguez<br><strong>Response Times</strong></p>
<p></p>
<p>Merge Requests must be requested to MR Approvers (see =E2=80=98Approvers=
=E2=80=99 section above) with at least<strong> </strong><em><strong>5 worki=
ng days</strong> in advance</em> to expected deployment date.</p>
<p></p>
<p>Note: This is critical mainly for Developers who do not belong to the ER=
P team nor report to any of MR Approver.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"GlobalGovernance|PD-GL-013ReleaseManagementProcess-Stepstodocumen=
taChangeinProduction"><strong>Steps to document a Change in Production</str=
ong></h3>
<p><strong>A. Receiving the Change Request</strong></p>
<p>The process begins when the User raises a ticket in <strong>Jira. </stro=
ng>This is the <strong>minimum information</strong> that needs to be includ=
ed in this request:&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Type of change</p></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Reason&nbsp;</p></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Business Impact / KPIs impact</p></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Expected Deployment Date</p></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Departments/Users impacted&nbsp;</p></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Request Details (brief description of the solution)</p></li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p>This should be approved or rejected by the User=E2=80=99s supervisor. Ap=
proval can be supported in an e-mail or add =E2=80=98OK=E2=80=99 as a comme=
nt in the Ticket.</p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>B. Functional and Technical Documentation</strong></p>
<p>This must be included in the documentation:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>&nbsp;<em>1. Priority and justification</em></p></li>
<li>
<p><em>2. Business Process</em></p></li>
<li>
<p><em>3. Product Owner&nbsp;</em></p></li>
<li>
<p><em>4. Problem Description&nbsp;</em></p></li>
<li>
<p><em>5. Proposed Solution</em></p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>C. Test Matrix / Test Cases</strong></p>
<p></p>
<p>Documentation should include:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Transaction Numbers that were generated for Testing purposes&nbsp;</p></=
li>
<li>
<p>Test results for each case</p></li>
<li>
<p>Print Screens</p></li>
<li>
<p>Users (Name, Email, Job Title)&nbsp; that participated in Testing</p></l=
i>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p>Tests must be executed in <u>QA environment (</u>not production)</p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>D. User Acceptance Test</strong></p>
<p></p>
<p>After Testing is concluded, User who requested the change must approve t=
he deployment based on Test Results.</p>
<p>This acceptance can be obtained in an e-mail that should be attached to =
the Jira Ticket, or the user can provide his/her OK/Approval as a comment i=
n the ticket.</p>
<p><u>This must be obtained prior to deployment in production</u></p>
<p></p>
<h3 id=3D"GlobalGovernance|PD-GL-013ReleaseManagementProcess-DeploymentExec=
ution"><strong>Deployment Execution</strong></h3>
<p>MR Approver receives the deployment request and reviews supporting docum=
entation. They must receive the request at least 5 working days prior to th=
e expected deployment date.</p>
<p></p>
<p>Approver can approve or reject the request based on the following criter=
ia: (examples)</p>
<p></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Lack of Test Evidence</p></li>
<li>
<p>Lack of UAT</p></li>
<li>
<p>No Business Impact in place&nbsp;</p></li>
<li>
<p>Incomplete documentation</p></li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p>If the MR is approved, they execute the deployment on the defined date.<=
/p>
<h3 id=3D"GlobalGovernance|PD-GL-013ReleaseManagementProcess-Rollback"><str=
ong>Rollback</strong></h3>
<p></p>
<p>After deployment in production is executed, functional and technical tea=
m must monitor if any issue affects the production environment. Suggested p=
eriod for monitoring is 3 working days.</p>
<p></p>
<p>If after the Monitoring Phase, it is confirmed that the business process=
 is in accordance with the solution, the ticket is closed.</p>
<p>This confirmation must be commented on the Jira ticket.</p>
<p></p>
